  "prompt": "Where can I get spring framework videos?",
  "response": "You can find Spring Framework videos from a variety of sources online. Here are some options:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Many developers and educators upload tutorials, walkthroughs, and lectures on the Spring Framework. You can search for specific topics within Spring, such as \"Spring Boot tutorial\" or \"Spring Security tutorial\".\n\n2. **Udemy**: This platform offers a range of paid courses on Spring Framework. These courses are often structured and comprehensive, covering various aspects of the framework.\n\n3. **Coursera**: You can find courses from universities and organizations that may include Spring Framework tutorials as part of their programming curriculum.\n\n4. **Pluralsight**: This is another platform that offers paid courses on Spring Framework. Pluralsight provides in-depth learning paths and assessments.\n\n5. **Spring.io**: The official website for Spring has a variety of guides and resources. Occasionally, they also provide video content and webinars.\n\n6. **EdX**: This platform offers courses on software development, some of which might include Spring Framework as part of their curriculum.\n\n7. **Java Brains**: This site (and YouTube channel) offers comprehensive and free tutorials on various Java frameworks, including Spring.\n\n8. **LinkedIn Learning**: This service offers professional courses on a wide range of topics, including Spring Framework. They also offer certificates upon completion.\n\nRemember to check reviews and ratings before committing to a paid course to ensure it meets your learning needs.",
